# Help: Kernel hardening baseline
#
# Stack protector (strong), FORTIFY_SOURCE (compile-time
# buffer-overflow detection via __builtin_object_size), hardened
# usercopy with default-on, SCHED_STACK_END_CHECK (kernel-stack
# overflow detection at schedule time), strict kernel/module text
# RWX separation, STRICT_DEVMEM (restricts /dev/mem to non-RAM).
# INIT_STACK_NONE and RANDSTRUCT_NONE pick the cheapest options
# from their Kconfig choice blocks; alternatives
# (INIT_STACK_ALL_ZERO, INIT_STACK_ALL_PATTERN, RANDSTRUCT_FULL)
# trade performance for defence-in-depth and can be layered via
# an ad-hoc override.
#
# Every symbol is bool. No builtin/ counterpart needed.
# See: security/Kconfig.hardening
# See: init/Kconfig (stackprotector)
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/admin-guide/hw-vuln/index.html

CONFIG_STACKPROTECTOR=y
CONFIG_STACKPROTECTOR_STRONG=y
CONFIG_FORTIFY_SOURCE=y
CONFIG_HARDENED_USERCOPY=y
CONFIG_HARDENED_USERCOPY_DEFAULT_ON=y
CONFIG_SCHED_STACK_END_CHECK=y
CONFIG_STRICT_KERNEL_RWX=y
CONFIG_STRICT_MODULE_RWX=y
CONFIG_STRICT_DEVMEM=y
CONFIG_INIT_STACK_NONE=y
CONFIG_RANDSTRUCT_NONE=y
